  "text": "## Prometheus Web UI Authentication Controls\n\n### Overview\nPrometheus implements web UI authentication through three mechanisms:\n\n1. **BasicAuth Middleware** - Handled by the exporter-toolkit via web configuration file\n2. **TLS Client Certificate Validation** - Configured via web configuration file passed to the exporter-toolkit\n3. **Admin API Access Control** - Controlled via the --web.enable-admin-api flag\n\n### Key Components\n\n#### 1. Command-Line Flags and Configuration (cmd/prometheus/main.go)\nThe main.go file defines the command-line flags that control authentication:\n- `--web.config.file`: Path to configuration file that can enable TLS or BasicAuth. The config file format is defined in the exporter-toolkit documentation and supports:\n  - `tls_server_config`: Defines server TLS settings including client certificate validation via `client_auth_type` and `client_ca_file`\n  - `basic_auth_users`: Maps usernames to bcrypt-hashed passwords for BasicAuth\n- `--web.enable-admin-api`: Boolean flag to enable/disable admin API endpoints\n\n#### 2. Web Server Setup (web/web.go)\nThe Handler struct in web/web.go serves as the main HTTP server:\n- The `Run()` method (line 722) sets up the HTTP server with multiple listeners\n- It calls `toolkit_web.ServeMultiple()` (line 760) which applies TLS and BasicAuth middleware from the exporter-toolkit\n- The webConfig file path is passed to the toolkit: `&toolkit_web.FlagConfig{WebConfigFile: &webConfig}`\n- The toolkit_web package from github.com/prometheus/exporter-toolkit/web handles:\n  - TLS certificate loading and validation\n  - Client certificate validation using the client_ca_file\n  - BasicAuth middleware that validates username/password against bcrypt-hashed users\n\n#### 3. Admin API Access Control (web/api/v1/api.go)\nThe API struct contains an `enableAdmin` field (line 241) that controls access to admin endpoints:\n\n**Admin API Endpoints:**\n- `POST/PUT /admin/tsdb/delete_series` - Implemented by `deleteSeries()` function (line 2026)\n- `POST/PUT /admin/tsdb/clean_tombstones` - Implemented by `cleanTombstones()` function (line 2093)\n- `POST/PUT /admin/tsdb/snapshot` - Implemented by `snapshot()` function (line 2059)\n\nEach admin function checks `if !api.enableAdmin` at the beginning and returns an \"admin APIs disabled\" error if the flag is not set.\n\nThe `NewAPI()` function (line 267) accepts the `enableAdmin` parameter and stores it in the API struct. This parameter is set from the `--web.enable-admin-api` flag in main.go.\n\n#### 4. HTTP Utilities (util/httputil/)\nThe httputil package provides supporting functionality:\n- `cors.go`: CORS header handling via `SetCORS()` function\n- `context.go`: Request context utilities\n- `compression.go`: Request/response compression handling\n\n### Authentication Flow\n\n1. **Request arrives at web server** → `web/web.go:Run()` handles listening\n2. **TLS/BasicAuth applied** → `toolkit_web.ServeMultiple()` middleware validates client certs and basic auth credentials\n3. **Request routed to API** → Routes registered in `web/api/v1/api.go:Register()`\n4. **Admin API access checked** → Functions check `api.enableAdmin` flag and return 503 error if disabled\n5. **Response returned** → Includes CORS headers if configured\n\n### Configuration Example\n\nWeb configuration file format (referenced by `--web.config.file`):\n```yaml\ntls_server_config:\n  cert_file: server.crt\n  key_file: server.key\n  client_auth_type: \"RequireAndVerifyClientCert\"\n  client_ca_file: client_ca.crt\n\nbasic_auth_users:\n  alice: $2y$10$mDwo.lAisC94iLAyP81MCesa29IzH37oigHC/42V2pdJlUprsJPze\n```\n\nCommand-line invocation:\n```bash\nprometheus --web.config.file=/etc/prometheus/web-config.yml --web.enable-admin-api\n```\n\n### Security Boundaries\n\nThe implementation follows these security patterns:\n1. **TLS and BasicAuth are enforced at the HTTP server level** via the exporter-toolkit, protecting all endpoints\n2. **Admin API is additionally gated by the enableAdmin flag** at the application level, requiring explicit opt-in\n3. **CORS is configurable** to prevent unauthorized cross-origin access\n4. **Client certificate validation** is supported for mutual TLS authentication between Prometheus and clients\n"
}

